This document excludes guidance on the design, structure, number and type of MDs to be installed in a continuous monitoring system.

This document describes a method for performing positron annihilation lifetime measurements using a 22Na positron source that decays with Î²+ emission. The Î²+ (positron) lifetime is determined from a measurement of the lifetime of the ortho-positronium which ranges from 1Â ns to 10Â ns (ascribed to a pore size from approximately 0,3Â nm to 1,3Â nm in diameter), as observed for polymeric materials in which the positronium atoms mostly annihilate via a two-gamma annihilation process. 
